- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses cryptographic algorithms and their vulnerabilities to side channel attacks. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the proposed countermeasure involves shuffling distributed switched capacitors, which is a hardware-level implementation. 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is another possible category as the paper discusses the extraction of secret keys from embedded devices. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions signal-to-noise (SNR) reduction, which is a common technique in machine learning. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is unlikely as the proposed countermeasure is a hardware-level implementation and does not involve software engineering.
